OL,3,CNI Children's Hospice to reduce bed
OL,4,Ccapacity due to 'loss of funding'
OL,6,FThe Northern Ireland Children's
OL,7,FHospice is to reduce its beds capacity
OL,8,Fdue to a "loss of government funding".
OL,10,FThe hospice in Glengormley, Co Antrim,
OL,11,Fprovides specialist palliative care
OL,12,Fsupporting more than 350 babies,
OL,13,Fchildren and their relatives each year.
OL,15,FThe service is the only one of its
OL,16,Fkind in Northern Ireland offering a
OL,17,Frange of vital services, including
OL,18,Fantenatal support and short breaks for
OL,19,Fterminally ill children and their
OL,20,Ffamilies.
