OL,4,Ccapacity due to 'loss of funding'
OL,6,F"I know we all will be concerned, we
OL,7,Fall would want to do our very, very
OL,8,Fbest for the hospice service itself,
OL,9,Fparticularly when you're dealing with
OL,10,Fchildren going through such a
OL,11,Fdifficult time," she said.
OL,13,F"I have spoken to the Health Minister,
OL,14,FI know that he and I, and I'm sure the
OL,15,Fdeputy First Minister, will want to do
OL,16,Feverything we can to be as supportive
OL,17,Fas we can of the hospice, and I have
OL,18,Fcommunicated that with them this
OL,19,Fmorning."
